<TITLE> North Korea's Kim greets soldiers for new year: agency </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 LONDON, Jan 3 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - North Korean leader Kim Jong-il has inspected a tank division and wished its soldiers a happy new year, state media said on Friday, days after news of his first major public outing since a suspected stroke in August. Kim, supreme commander of the Korean People's Army among other titles, inspected Guard Seoul Ryu Kyong Su Tank Division 105 "and congratulated its servicepersons on the new year", reported the state news agency KCNA, monitored in London. The visit would be a fresh public engagement for Kim after reports of illness raised questions about leadership in the world's first communist dynasty and about who was in charge of its nuclear arms programme. Kim went to a concert where the audience cheered him, official media said on Monday, without stating when this was. South Korea said it was his first appearance at a mass public event since the suspected stroke. Speculation about Kim's health peaked in September when he did not appear at a triumphal military parade to mark 60 years since the founding of the state by his father Kim Il-sung. Over the past few months, the North has sought to show Kim as active and in control after the reports of his illness, with state media issuing several similar reports of field guidance visits to military units, factories and farms
